metadata.name: Look Me In the Eye
metadata.description:
This portrait of Eagle Owl was created by me around October 2020, a painting is acrylic on paper.

it was the firs painting of a small series called Incorporating Colors. 

The artwork was created at first in neon pink and then I added more natural colors.

I wanted to express that even in the things that may seem reserved, or dark, or gloomy (though I don't think owls are any of the above) - 
You can add your meaning, your attitude to the things around you.
And there's a lot of emotional color in any everyday matter.
